BLACK BEAN CHILI

1 2lb round steak
½ green pepper
1 T. oregano
1/4 tsp cayenne
1 small can diced green chiles
2 cans black beans

1 med onion
1 T cumin
2 tsp paprika
1 T crushed garlic
1 lg can tomatoes
1 pkg flour tortillas

toast oregano, cayenne & cumin in skillet, stirring constantly to avoid burning; saute onion, garlic and green
pepper; add drained tomatoes (discard juice), black beans, sautéed mixture and spices and simmer 30 minutes to an
hour; bar-b-que steak (sirloin is best), cube and add to mixture along with chiles and salt and pepper to taste,
serve with grated cheese and brown tortillas.
